    • Field Detail

      • cliponaxis

        @Option
public Boolean cliponaxis
        Determines whether or not markers and text nodes are clipped about the subplot axes. To show markers and text nodes above axis lines and tick labels, make sure to set "xaxis.layer" and "yaxis.layer" to "below traces".

      • connectgaps

        @Option
public Boolean connectgaps
        Determines whether or not gaps (i.e. {nan} or missing values) in the provided data arrays are connected.

      • fill

        @Option
public FillAreaEnum fill
        The area to fill with a solid color. Only NONE, TONEXT and TOSELF are recognized.

      • fillcolor

        @Option
public String fillcolor
        The fill color.

        Default: A half-transparent variant of the line color, marker color, or marker line color, whichever is available.

      • hoveron

        @Option
public String hoveron
        Any combination of "points", "fills" joined with a "+" examples: "points", "fills", "points+fills" Do the hover effects highlight individual points (markers or line points) or do they highlight filled regions? If the fill is "toself" or "tonext" and there are no markers or text, then the default is "fills", otherwise it is "points".

      • hovertext$array

        @Option(value="hovertext")
public String[] hovertext$array
        Hover text elements associated with each (x,y) pair as an array of strings where the items are mapped in order to the this trace's (x,y) coordinates. To be seen, trace "hoverinfo" must contain a "text" flag.

      • hovertext$string

        @Option(value="hovertext")
public String hovertext$string
        Hover text elements associated with each (x,y) pair as a single string where the same string appears over all the data points. To be seen, trace "hoverinfo" must contain a "text" flag.

      • line

        @Option
public final LineOptions line
        The line options.

      • marker

        @Option
public final MarkerOptions marker
        Options for marker.

      • mode

        @Option
public String mode
        Any combination of "lines", "markers", "text" joined with a "+" OR "none". examples: "lines", "markers", "lines+markers", "lines+markers+text", "none" Determines the drawing mode for this scatter trace. If the provided "mode" includes "text" then the "text" elements appear at the coordinates. Otherwise, the "text" elements appear on hover. If there are less than 20 points, then the default is "lines+markers". Otherwise, "lines".

      • r

        @Option
public double[] r
        The radial coordinates

      • selected

        @Option
public final SelectedOptions selected

      • subplot

        @Option
public String subplot
        Reference between this trace's data coordinates and a polar subplot. If "polar" (the default value), the data refer to "layout.polar". If "polar2", the data refer to "layout.polar2", and so on.

      • text$array

        @Option(value="text")
public String[] text$array
        Text elements associated with each (x,y) pair as an array of strings where the items are mapped in order to the this trace's (x,y) coordinates. If trace "hoverinfo" contains a "text" flag and "hovertext" is not set, these elements will be seen in the hover labels.

      • text$string

        @Option(value="text")
public String text$string
        Text elements associated with each (x,y) pair as a single string where the same string appears over all the data points. If trace "hoverinfo" contains a "text" flag and "hovertext" is not set, these elements will be seen in the hover labels.

      • textfont

        @Option
public final FontOptions textfont
        The text font.

      • textposition

        @Option
public TextPositionEnum textposition
        The positions of the "text" elements with respects to the (x,y) coordinates. Defaults to TOP_CENTER.

      • theta

        @Option
public double[] theta
        The angular coordinates

      • thetaunit

        @Option
public PolarUnitsEnum thetaunit
        The unit of input "theta" values. Has an effect only when on "linear" angular axes. Defaults to DEGREES.

      • unselected

        @Option
public final SelectedOptions unselected
